111.title: Study Abroad Information & Poster Fair
111.EventDesc:
Do you think you might be interested in studying abroad next academic year (Fall 2020 or Spring 2021)? Attend the Study Abroad Information & Poster Fair on September 11th, anytime from 10am - 3pm in Seegers 111-113!
 Pick up the approved program list of over 160 different short- and long-term study abroad options;
 Speak with program, student, and faculty representatives;
 See students' posters about their experience; and
 Begin mentally preparing for the study abroad application deadline in December 2019.
 If you are an athlete, learn how you can continue your off-season workout regimen while abroad.

First year students, Sophomores, and Juniors are welcome to attend, as are Faculty and Staff!

763.title: Posadas
763.EventDesc: Posadas will take place on Tuesday 3 December from 7-8:30 pm. We will start at the CA, then move on to Seegers, then on to the Chaplain's house, then end up at the President's house, with Latin holiday treats at our last two stops, generously funded by the President's office. What are Posadas? They are a song cycle from 16th century Mexico. They are similar to carols, in that a group of singers moves from one home to another.Posadas they are different in that they follow the Advent story of the refugee family of Mary and Joseph as they travel through foreign lands in search of a place where Mary can have here child --that would be the baby Jesus!-- in safety and whatever comfort they can find. The songs recount the pleas for shelter, the rejection that followed, and eventually, the welcoming of this migrant family. Por supuesto, this is a powerful reminder of today's situation of migrants crossing borders and facing hostility... with a happy ending that we hope will inspire us all. Plus, the music is truly lovely.
